description.narrative:
1. Phase one: A Review of the current Monitoring and Evaluation framework and proposal to the integration of child indicators;
2. Phase two:  Methodology and tools to collect data on the proposed child indicators;
3. Phase three: Capacity building materials and Training of Trainers list of attendees;
4. Phase four: A reporting tool to regularly monitor child and;
5. Phase five: A plan to collect data, define baseline, and conduct future evaluation of program impact on children.

comment.narrative:
1. Phase one: Need for a Review on the current Monitoring and Evaluation framework and a proposal on the integration of child indicators;
2. Phase two: Need for an institutionalized methodology and tools to collect data on the proposed child indicators;
3. Phase three: Need for capacity building materials and conduction a Training of Trainers on the use of proposed M&E tools;
4. Phase four: Need for an institutionalized reporting tool to regularly monitor child and
5. Phase five: Need for a plan to collect data, define baseline, and conduct future evaluation of program impact on children.

1. Phase one: 0
2. Phase two: Develop and assist the Ministry to institutionalize the methodology and tools to collect data on the proposed child indicators;
3. Phase three: Develop capacity building materials and conduct a Training of Trainers on the use of proposed M&E tools;
4. Phase four: Develop and assist the Ministry to institutionalize a reporting tool to regularly monitor child and;
5. Phase five: Develop a plan to collect data, define baseline, and conduct future evaluation of program impact on children.

1. Phase one: 0 

2. Phase two: Concluded - The main deliverable of Phase 2 should have been a Draft of a technical guiding manual on methodology and tools. However, due to the specific demand of the Minister (see 2.2), the delay in getting access to data and to the low level of remote engagement of the Egyptian Counterparts, this deliverable was not elaborated and
was replaced by a series of draft documents:
Delivered on the second mission:
• Advocacy document and proposal for monitoring the educational outcomes of beneficiary children;
Delivered on the third mission:
• draft document on beneficiaries module indicators;
• draft document on education indicators; 
• presentation on the challenges to monitor health outcomes;
• draft document on antenatal care to map what could be monitored;
Delivered by December 2017:
• Reporting tool v.1 with Manual;



3. Phase three: Concluded - The training of trainers did not happen as expected. The event was not well organised, and the people selected to participate in the training were mostly IT staff not directly engaged in programme manage and not
knowledgeable about social protection or monitoring (actually, only one of the trainees had the right profile).
Furthermore, computers were not prepared in advance, thus all software used had to be downloaded and the
meeting room reserved for the training did not count with internet connection. An additional problem was
that some of the computers were old and slow, and the users did not had privileges to install software in their
computer. The training was, nevertheless, delivered. Also, as the training of trainers was not successful, it was decided that another training would be held after the final version of the Reporting Tool was made available, this time to train the people who would extract the indicators using the Reporting Tool on writing the Reports (based on the Report Models developed in Phase 4);

4. Phase four: Concluded - All deliverables of this phase were concluded and sent to Unicef Egypt by September 5 2018. They were presented to and discussed with MoSS during the fifth mission Unfortunately, due to government
disengagement, the training of report writers using the Brief and Profile Report Samplers and their respective
training materials did not happen. The Reporting Tool, as developed by IPC, was not implemented as a web
app in the Ministry intranet, in spite of being delivered to MoSS.
DELIVERABLES:
• Reporting Tool and demonstration website in English and Arabic;
• Brief Report and training material on how to elaborate Briefs with the Reporting Tool;
• Profile Report and training material on how to elaborate Profiles with the Reporting Tool;

5. Phase five: Concluded - All deliverables of this phase were concluded and sent by Unicef Egypt to MoSS in August 29 2018.
DELIVERABLES
• Advisory note on monitoring of conditionalities – Education;
• Advisory note on monitoring of conditionalities – Health
